# CASPER Authenticator Project Rules

## Project Overview
This is a CASPER-based authenticator implementation with Android app and Spring Boot backends.

## Code Style
- Use Java 17+ features
- Follow Android coding conventions
- Use meaningful variable names
- Add Javadoc comments for public methods
- Keep methods focused and single-purpose

## Security Practices
- Never log sensitive data (PINs, private keys)
- Use secure random number generation
- Validate all user inputs
- Use HTTPS in production
- Store secrets securely (Android Keystore)

## Project Structure
- Android app: `app/src/main/java/com/casper/authenticator/`
- PMS backend: `pms-backend/casper-pms/`
- RP backend: `rp-backend/casper-rp/`

## Testing
- Test CASPER breach detection scenarios
- Verify encryption/decryption flows
- Test network error handling

